=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_LFCub_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A dark gritty sound, with noise oscillator character around 954 Hz, featuring punchy attack and sustained envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally sparse.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: dark
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: gritty
  spectral_complexity_mean: sparse
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 954.1213
  harmonic_decay_rate: -10.7065
  harmonic_regularity: 0.7930
  pitch_clarity: 25.2105
  inharmonicity: 0.3023
  type: noise
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -21.5752
  resonance_freq: 818.2617

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: LFCub Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/LFCub.html
// Tags: LFCub, Classes
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
{ LFCub.ar(LFCub.kr(LFCub.kr(0.2, 0, 8, 10), 0, 400, 800), 0, 0.1) }.play
{ LFCub.ar(LFCub.kr(0.2, 0, 400, 800), 0, 0.1) }.play
{ LFCub.ar(800, 0, 0.1) }.play
{ LFCub.ar(XLine.kr(100, 8000, 30), 0, 0.1) }.play

